get_samplesets_ranking

Source: R/queries.R
get_samplesets_ranking.Rd

get_samplesets_ranking

get_samplesets_ranking(
  compendium = "vespucci",
  version = "legacy",
  rankTarget = "samplesets",
  rank = "magnitude",
  biofeaturesNames = NULL,
  biofeaturesIds = NULL,
  top_n = 50
)

Arguments

compendium

a character - the selected compendium
version

a character ('legacy' as default)
rankTarget

a character ('sampleset' as default)
rank

a character ('magnitude' as default)
biofeatureNames

a character vector (here gene_names)
biofeatureIds

a character vector (here gene_ids)

Value

a list with four character vectors (id,name,type,value)

Examples

my_ids <- c("VIT_00s0332g00110","VIT_00s0332g00160","VIT_00s0396g00010","VIT_00s0505g00030")
get_samplesets_ranking(biofeaturesNames = my_ids)
